File: The Hawks say it will issue a statement on the matter soon. CAPE TOWN - The Hawks says it expects to make arrests in connection with COVID-19 corruption. The Hawks told Parliament's Standing Committee on Public Accounts that the arrests are expected on Thursday in connection with PPE tender fraud. READ: Hawks official says he's being smeared It also wants to freeze about R26-million allegedly attained unlawfully. Some 20 cases linked to COVID-19 fraud and corruption have been referred to the National Prosecuting Authority. Meanwhile, disciplinary action has been recommended for officials in 12 cases.